2^{-18}
\Phi(23)=22
  \text{The inverse of $2^{18}$ is $2^{-18}$. The modulus in the exponent is $\Phi(23)=22$.}\\ 2^{-18} = 2^{-18+22} = 2^4 = 16 \ mod \ 23 
 a^{-1} = a^{\phi(23)-1} \rightarrow 2^{18*(22-1)} = 2^{18*21} = 16 \ mod \ 23 
